                        h3#our_commitment_to_privacy.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Our Commitment to Privacy
                        p.pb10 At GrowthFountain, our most important asset is our relationship with you.
                        p.pb10 This Privacy Policy answers some questions about what information we collect, what we do with it, and how we protect it.  It also describes the choices available to you regarding our use of your personal information.
                        p.pb10 We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy in its entirety since any use of the sites or services offered by GrowthFountain will be governed by the practices and policies outlined in this Privacy Policy.  You expressly consent to our collection, storage, use, and disclosure of your personal information in the manner described in this Privacy Policy. 
                        p.pb10 As used in this Privacy Policy, “GrowthFountain”, “we”, “us”, and/or "our" means GrowthFountain Capital LLC, a company registered as a funding portal with the Securities and Exchange Commission.  This Privacy Policy covers information that may be shared with our affiliates, joint marketers, regulatory agencies and other third parties.
                        
                        h3#application_of_our_policy.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Application of Our Policy
                        p.pb10 This Privacy Policy applies to (a) information collected in connection with your access to, use of, or interaction with, the web site www.GrowthFountain.com and related domains, subdomains and observable web pages, including without limitation joint marketing websites that are hosted by GrowthFountain (collectively, the “Site”); (b) information collected in connection with GrowthFountin providing you with any products or services related to the Site or arising out of your participation in, or your indication of interest to participate in, any offer or sale of securities under Section 4(a)(6) of the Securities Act of 1933 in connection with Regulation Crowdfunding (collectively, the “Services”) and (c) information collected in connection with GrowthFountain’s performance of any identification procedures, security checks or regulatory compliance activities, including any analysis, tracking, correlating or aggregating of data derived from such activities (collectively, “Security Activities”).
                        p.pb10 This Privacy Policy applies to business operators and entrepreneurs seeking to raise capital through the Site, to investors evaluating securities listed on the Site, to individuals seeking information on crowdfunding and to all other users of the Site or any of the Services (in each case, a "User").  With respect to each such User, this Privacy Policy covers GrowthFoutain’s treatment of personally identifiable information collected about such User that is gathered at any time (collectively, "Personal Data"). 
                        
                        h3#information_we_collect.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Information We Collect
                        p.pb10 The information we gather enables us to process your requests, communicate with you, and improve both out Site and our Services. When you interact with us through the Site or the Services, we may collect Personal Data and other information from you, including the categories and types of information described below:
                        ul
                            li
                                u Usage Data.
                                |  We receive and store certain types of information whenever you interact with our Site or Services. GrowthFountain automatically receives and records information on our server logs from your browser, including your IP address, and the page you requested. Our service automatically collects usage information, such as the frequency of visitation to the Site.  As is true of most web sites, we also gather other information automatically such as browser type, internet service provider (ISP), referring/exit pages, operating system, date/time stamp, and clickstream data. GrowthFountain may store such information itself or such information may be included in databases owned and maintained by GrowthFountain affiliates, agents or service providers.
                            li
                                u Voluntary Data.  
                                |  We collect Personal Data from you when you voluntarily provide such information.  For example, when you register for access to the Site or the Services, we may collect contact information (such as your name, email address, phone number, and mailing address), financial information (such as bank account numbers), and identifying information (such as your date of birth and social security number).  We may also collect information that you provide to us when contacting us with inquiries, or responding to one of our surveys.
                            li
                                u Screening Data.  
                                |  We may collect information from you or third parties in connection with any background check, security procedures or similar compliance related activities.  This information may contain Personal Data or be combined with your Personal Data.
                            li
                                u Research and Feedback Data.
                                |  GrowthFountain may conduct research on a User’s demographics, interests and other identifying characteristics based on the Personal Data and other information provided to GrowthFountain.  We may also collect information from surveys and other interactive campaigns designed to generate User feedback.
                            li
                                u Aggregated Data.  
                                |  GrowthFountain may aggregate data with its affiliates, joint marketers, agents and business partners. GrowthFountain may disclose aggregated user statistics in order to describe our Services to current and prospective business partners and to other third parties for other lawful purposes.  You understand and agree that we may provide aggregate information to our partners about how Users interact with the Site. You also understand that we share this type of statistical data with joint marketing partners to provide a metric for the effectiveness of specific marketing campaigns. 
                            li
                                u Transaction Data.
                                |  When you participate in any offer or sale of securities on the Site, we receive and store certain information about you related to such transaction.  When you accept any offers, products or services offered by third parties or joint marketers advertising on the Site, we may generate, exchange or receive certain information related to any transactions arising therefrom.

                        h3#use_of_cookies.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Use of Cookies
                        p.pb10 In operating this Site, we may use a technology called "cookies."  Cookies are small files that we transfer to your computer's hard drive to help analyze the Site’s web page flow, customize our Services, measure promotional effectiveness, and promote trust and safety. Most browsers have an option for turning off the cookie feature, which will prevent your browser from accepting new cookies. We recommend that you leave the cookies activated, however, because cookies enable you to take advantage of some of our website's features, and you may not be able to access certain areas of the Site or certain Services if your cookies are not activated.  The use of cookies by our affiliates or service providers is not covered by this Privacy Policy since we do not have access or control over these cookies.
                        p.pb10 We may also use or employ technologies similar to cookies to provide our Services and help collect data. You agree that we may use cookies and other similar technologies to allow us to collect information and, among other things, to store your preferences and settings; to enable you to sign-in; to speed access to portions of the Site, to provide interest-based advertising; to combat fraud; and to analyze how our Services are performing.

                        h3#personal_data.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Our Use of Your Personal Data and Other Information
                        p.pb10 GrowthFountain may use your Personal Data and other personally non-identifiable information collected through the Site to help us improve the content and functionality of the Site, to better understand our Users and to improve the Services. GrowthFountain may use this information to communicate with you regarding the Services, to tell you about services we believe will be of interest to you or to provide administrative communications that are reasonably necessary to the Service.  GrowthFountain uses your Personal Data to comply with applicable law and to perform the activities of a funding portal.
                        p.pb10 GrowthFountain may collect, analyze and assess aggregated user statistics in order to describe our Services to current and prospective business partners and to other third parties for other lawful purposes.  We also may share data with affiliates and with vendors working on our behalf to protect our customers or to maintain the security of the Site and our Services.
                        p.pb10 We may release Personal Data when we believe in good faith that release is necessary to comply with the law or to enforce or apply our terms of use and other agreements. This includes exchanging information with other companies and organizations for fraud protection and risk reduction.
                        p.pb10 In general, you agree that the following are permitted purposes for collecting information: (a) to understand your needs, (b) to keep improving the Site and Service, (c) for internal record keeping, (d) to communicate with you regarding information which we think you may find interesting, (e) to contact you for market research purposes, (f) to customize the Site according to your interests, (g) to comply with law and make assessments regarding the potential for fraud, abuse or violation of law, (h) to process payments and transactions, (i) to respond to your requests and (j) to customize the advertising and content you see.

                        h3#disclosure_personal_data.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Our Disclosure of Your Personal Data and Other Information
                        p.pb10 We may on occasion share your Personal Data in certain limited circumstances.  You agree that in order to provide the Site and Services, we may employ third parties to perform tasks on our behalf and in such circumstances may need to share your Personal Data with them to provide products or services to you. For example, we use a third party escrow agent in connection with holding certain investor funds and in doing so we are required to exchange information that may identify you or your Personal Data.  For other activities, such as reducing fraud and ensuring the identity of certain Users, we may also use third parties with whom we might share Personal Data.  You agree that we may use the Personal Data to obtain additional information about you from third party sources or to verify your identity so we can properly process your requests and reduce fraud. By accessing our Site and using our Services, you hereby explicitly consent that we may use your submitted and obtained Personal Data for such purposes.
                        p.pb10 The following list describes the types of circumstances in which we may share your Personal Data and other information with certain third parties without further notice to you:
                        ul
                            li
                                u Securities Transaction Disclosure.  
                                |  We may share your Personal Data with counterparties in connection with our effecting a securities transaction as a registered funding portal.  For example, we may share information with a third party transfer agent in connection with a securities transaction.
                            li
                                u Related Company Disclosure.
                                |  We may share your Personal Data with our wholly owned affiliates for purposes consistent with this Privacy Policy.
                            li
                                u Disclosure to Agents or Consultants.  
                                |  GrowthFountain, like many businesses, sometimes hires other companies to perform certain business-related functions. Examples of such functions include maintaining databases, ID verification, escrow services, processing payments and completing transactions. When we employ another company to perform a function of this nature, we only provide them with the information that they need to perform their specific function. These companies are authorized to use your personal information only as necessary to provide these services to us.
                            li
                                u Disclosure to Joint Marketers
                                |  GrowthFountain may enter into joint marketing agreements in which we may provide Personal Data to measure the effectiveness of the joint marketing efforts. Examples of such disclosure includes reporting to any third-parties the number of individuals that signed up on the Site based on a referral from such third-party. 
                            li
                                u Required Disclosures
                                |  GrowthFountain may disclose your Personal Data if required to do so by law or if we have the good faith belief that such action is necessary to (i) comply with a legal obligation, (ii) protect and defend the rights or property of GrowthFountain, (iii) act in urgent circumstances to protect the personal safety of users of the Site or the public against fraud or other harm, or (iv) protect against legal liability.
                            li
                                u Business Transaction Disclosure. 
                                |  In the event of a corporate sale, merger, reorganization, dissolution or similar event for GrowthFountain, Personal Data may be part of the transferred assets and, to the extent reasonably practicable, you may be notified as to any choices you may have regarding your personal information that may be transferred.

                        h3#security.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Security
                        p.pb10 The security of your personal information is important to us.  Your password and log-in credentials are a critical component of keeping your information safe and we expect you not to disclose your password to anyone. If you do share your password or personal information with others, you are responsible for all actions taken in the name of your account. 
                        p.pb10 While we try to ensure that your information is secure on our system, no data transmission over the internet can be guaranteed to be 100% secure.  Although we work hard to protect your privacy, Personal Data transmitted through the internet is likely to generate some risk that such data may be intercepted, hacked, hijacked or otherwise obtained without your consent or knowledge.
                        p.pb10 We follow generally accepted standards to protect the personal information submitted to us, both during transmission and once we receive it.

                        h3#exclusions.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Exclusions
                        p.pb10 This Privacy Policy does not apply to any information provided to GrowthFountain that was intended to be shared publically, including without limitation information made available through the internet or on the Site in connection with any disclosure required by applicable law.  For example, this Privacy Policy does not apply to any messages posted on the communications channels which are publicly available on the Site.  Additionally, this Privacy Policy does not apply to any comments posted to any of the blogs or other content available on the Site.  This Privacy Policy also does not apply to any of the information contained in the Form C required by Regulation CrowdFunding or any of the offering material filed publically with any governmental or regulatory body.
                        p.pb10 Any ideas for new products or modifications to existing products, and other unsolicited submissions shall be deemed to be non-confidential and GrowthFountain shall be free to reproduce, use, disclose, distribute and exploit such information without limitation or attribution.
                        p.pb10 This Privacy Policy does not apply to any social media posts that are made available publically on the internet.  It also does not apply to any testimonials that we may post on the Site or otherwise publicize, provided that you have given consent for such use.  You agree that any such consent is irrevocable once obtained.

                        h3#voluntary_disclosure.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Voluntary Disclosure
                        p.pb10 By voluntarily providing us with Personal Data, you are consenting to our use of it in accordance with this Privacy Policy. If you provide Personal Data, you acknowledge and agree that such Personal Data may be transferred from your current location to the offices and servers of GrowthFountain and the authorized third parties referred to herein.
                        p.pb10 You understand that you may opt not to disclose information provided that you discontinue your use of the Site and Services. You acknowledge and agree that GrowthFountain has regulatory obligations that require the collection of certain information and that discontinuing your access to the Site and Services is an appropriate and reasonable response should you ever opt to refrain from disclosing information that GrowthFountain determines is necessary for compliance with applicable law or for otherwise managing risk.  

                        h3#social_media_features.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Social Media Features
                        p.pb10 You can log in to our site using sign-in services such as Facebook Connect or LinkedIn. These services will authenticate your identity and provide you the option to share certain personal information with us such as your name and email address to pre-populate our sign up form. We may use or add other sign-in services in the future, and some of those services, like Facebook Connect, may give you the option to post information about your activities to share with others within your network. Any publically available social media posts are not covered by this Privacy Policy.
                        p.pb10 The Site may also include social media features that may collect information about you (such as your IP address or which page you are visiting on our site). Some of these social media features, tools and widgets may be hosted by a third party and in such cases, your interactions with these social media features will be governed by the privacy policy of the company providing it.

                        h3#minors.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Minors
                        p.pb10 Use of the Site and the Services is limited to those persons who are over 18 years of age.  GrowthFountain does not knowingly collect or solicit Personal Data from children under the age of 13 or knowingly allow children under the age of 13 to register. If you are under the age of 13, please do not submit any Personal Data through the Site. We encourage parents and legal guardians to monitor their children's internet usage and to help enforce our Privacy Policy by instructing their children never to provide Personal Data on this Site without their permission. In the event that we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under age 13 without verification of parental consent, we will take action to remove or delete that information as quickly as possible. If you have reason to believe that a child under the age of 13 has provided Personal Data to GrowthFountain through this Site, please contact us at
                            a(href="mailto:info@growthfountain.com").link-1  info@growthfountain.com 
                            |  so that we can investigate the matter.


                        h3#links_to_other_web_sites.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Links to Other Web Sites
                        p.pb10 The Site may contain links to other web sites not operated or controlled by GrowthFountain (collectively, "Third Party Sites"). The policies and procedures we described here do not apply to Third Party Sites. The links from this Site do not imply that GrowthFountain endorses or has reviewed any Third Party Sites. We suggest contacting those sites directly for information on their privacy policies.
                        p.pb10 Once you have used links to leave the Site, you understand that we cannot be responsible for the protection and privacy of any information which you provide whilst visiting such sites and such sites are not governed by this Privacy Policy. You should exercise caution and look at the privacy statement applicable to the website in question.

                        h3#changes_to_this_privacy_policy.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Changes to this Privacy Policy
                        p.pb10 We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes to our information practices. If we make any changes, we will change the last updated date at the top of this Privacy Policy. We encourage you to periodically review this page for the latest information on our privacy practices.  We will post changes to this Privacy Policy as well as annual reporting on our Privacy Policy on the Site and other places we deem appropriate. 

                        h3#changes_to_collected_information.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Changes to Collected Information
                        p.pb10 We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes to our information practices. If we make any changes we will change the last updated date at the top of this page. We encourage you to periodically review this page for the latest information on our privacy practices.  We will post changes to this Privacy Policy as well as annual reporting on our Privacy Policy on the Site and other places we deem appropriate. 

                        h3#contacting_us.text-uppercase.dosis.m-t-0.m-b-1.text-xs-center Contacting Us
                        p.pb10 If you have any comments or questions about GrowthFountain's Privacy Policy or the information practices of the Site, please feel free to contact us at info@growthfountain.com or by mail at:
                        p GrowthFountain LLC
                        p 75 Chambers Street, Suite 6
                        p.pb10 New York, NY 10007
                        p.pb10 If your personal information changes, you may correct, update, amend, delete or request deletion by making the change in your registered account settings page or by emailing our Customer Support at 
                            a(href="mailto:info@GrowthFountain.com").link-1 info@GrowthFountain.com.
                        p.pb10 We will retain your information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide you services. We will retain and use your information as necessary to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. You may be able to add or update certain information the we have collected. When you update information, however, we often maintain a copy of the unrevised information in our records. Please note that some information may remain in our records after deletion of your account.
                        p.pb10 You acknowledge and agree that GrowthFountain may be required to collect certain information in connection with applicable law.  There is no ability to opt-out of our collecting this information or any related information required to authenticate your identity or otherwise perform security and compliance functions.
                        p.pb10 We may also send you information on offer and promotions.  These forms of marketing material will have opt out language contained in the communication.  Please note, however, there is no way to opt out of electronic communications in their entirety since Regulation Crowdfunding requires the ability to send material electronically.  Consequently, while there may be some marketing pieces that you will be able to avoid, you should not have any expectation that you will be able to curtail the use of your email account for electronic delivery of documents and notices related to the Site or the Service.
                        p.pb10 You agree to opt-out limitation described above and further agree that such limitation is supported by sufficient consideration in terms of your ability to access and use the Site.  To the extent that you wish to limit the collection of information, you will need to close your account and cease using the Site and the Services.
                        p.pb10 We may send you service-related announcements when it is necessary or appropriate to do so.  For instance, if our service is temporarily suspended for maintenance, we might send you an email.  Generally, you may not opt-out of these communications, which are not promotional in nature.  If you do not wish to receive them, you have the option to deactivate your account.
                        p.pb10 You do not have the right to request access to the personal information that we record about you.  Your rights are limited to receiving electronic copies of the documents that you have electronically signed. 
                        p.pb10 To obtain access to these documents, you can visit your account settings for electronic download or you can email us for assistance at info@growthfountain.com.  Any request should include your name, address, telephone number, and the recorded information to which you would like access.  We may assess certain fees relating to any delivery charges that arise in responding to your request.















